author: William J. Gedney
notes: Hudak, Thomas J., and William J. Gedney. 2010. William J. Gedney's concise Saek-English, English-Saek lexicon. Oceanic Linguistics special publication, no. 37. Honolulu: University of Hawai'i Press.The Saek tones are:1 = /34/ mid level, slight rise at the end2 = /11/ low level3 = /31/ falling to low, with glottal constriction4 = /454/ high rising-falling5 = /52/ high falling6 = /32/ mid level, with slight fall and glottal constriction
